When Jesus cooks breakfast for his disciples on the shore of the Sea of Galilee (John 21:1-14), he says, "Come and have breakfast". He also instructs them, "Bring some of the fish you've just caught," and later serves them, saying "Come and eat breakfast".Key details from this post-resurrection story in John 21 include:The Invitation: Jesus has a charcoal fire with fish and bread already prepared for them.The Conversation: While eating, none of the disciples dared to ask "Who are you?" because they knew it was the Lord.The Follow-up: After breakfast, Jesus asks Peter, "Do you love me?" three times to reconcile him.This intimate scene highlights Jesus' resurrection in a physical body and his care for the disciples

